%matplotlib inline

from decoder import *
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from coldict import *
from scipy import stats

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

def read_coordinates(fout, method = 'poincare'):
#     we saved sampled coordinates to reproduce the exact plots from the paper
    df = pd.read_csv(f'{fout}_coordinates_{method}_interpolated.csv', sep=',')
    n = len(df.columns)
    x = np.double(df.values[:, 0:n - 1])
    labels = df.values[:, (n - 1)]
    labels = labels.astype(str)
    return x, labels

def save_coordinates(embed_coord, method):
    df = pd.DataFrame(embed_coord, columns=['x1', 'x2'])
    df['labels'] = true_labels_interpolate
    df.to_csv(f"{fout}_coordinates_{method}_interpolated.csv", index=False, sep=',')

Compare in terms of pseudotime¶

In [23]:
head_idx = np.where(true_labels_full == root_type)[0]
D = pairwise_distances(data_full[head_idx, :], metric='euclidean')
iroot = head_idx[np.argmin(D.sum(axis=0))]
adata_full = sc.AnnData(data_full)
adata_full.var_names = col_names
adata_full.obs['labels'] = true_labels_full
adata_full.uns['iroot'] = iroot
sc.pp.neighbors(adata_full, n_neighbors=30)
sc.tl.diffmap(adata_full)
sc.tl.dpt(adata_full)
dpt_true = np.array(adata_full.obs['dpt_pseudotime'])
dpt_true[dpt_true == np.inf] = 1.2
